d by upstream/downstream delays.\n\n4. **High Error Rates:**\n   - `Frontend` services across different nodes experienced high `HTTP status code: 500` errors. This was not limited to one pod, indicating a systemic issue likely propagated through shared dependencies like `checkoutservice`.\n\n5. **CartService Spike:**\n   - Noteworthy latency increase in `CheckoutService` -> `CartService` `GetCart` operations, jumping from 8,453 microseconds to 606,526 microseconds, indicating a potential bottleneck here.\n\n### Hypotheses\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\n    \"rrt_max\",\n    \"checkoutservice->checkoutservice\",\n    \"frontend->checkoutservice\",\n    \"checkoutservice->cartservice\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"PlaceOrder operation latency drastically increased from 152118 μs to 1134773.5 μs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice->cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"GetCart operation latency spiked from 8453 μs to 606526 μs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"error_ratio\",\n      \"evidence\": \"High frequency of HTTP 500 errors across all frontend instances.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThe most plausible root cause is the delay within the `checkoutservice`, particularly impacting operations related to order processing. The errors propagated quickly through `frontend` services, causing a high rate of HTTP 500 errors. It would be beneficial to investigate `checkoutservice` resources, database interactions, and potential load issues related to `CartService`."}
